PERTH (miningweekly.com) â€“ Diamond miner Lucapa has recovered a 138 ct diamond from Mining Block 46 at its Lulo operation, in Angola. The ASX-listed company on Thursday said that this was the seventh diamond of more than 100 ct to be recovered in 2021 so far, and the twenty-fourth stone of more than 100 ct to be recovered at Lulo since exploration and mining operations began. In January this year, the company recovered a 113 ct gem-quality diamond from Lulo in the same area.